article.headline: Dowell scores 22, Texas-Arlington tops Troy 59-56
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- Reger Dowell hit a pair of 3-pointers in the final 29 seconds and scored 16 of his 22 points in the second half while leading Texas-Arlington past Troy 59-56 Thursday night. Dowell came into the game ranked 11th nationally and 1st in the Sun Belt Conference in scoring at 21.6 per game. Jamel Outler added 10 points and Brandon Edwards pulled down 12 rebounds for the Mavericks (8-10, 3-3 Sun Belt Conference). Edwards moved into 6th on the school's all-time rebounding list with 709. Dowell's 3-pointer with 29 seconds to play made it 56-53. Hunter Williams, who paced Troy (7-12, 2-5) with 19 points, answered with a 3 of his own 15 seconds later. Dowell made it 59-56 with another trey with 5 seconds to play before Williams missed a 3-pointer with 1 second remaining. Jeff Mullahey scored 12 points for the Mavericks, who shot 34 percent from the floor.
